## Benchmark Pack Loader

Create:

```text
src/engine/benchmarks/shared/benchmarkPackLoader.ts
```

Responsibilities:
- load built-in packs
- load installed user packs
- parse `pack.json`
- validate packs
- return usable packs
- report invalid packs clearly
- never crash the app because of one bad pack

Public functions:

```ts
loadBuiltInBenchmarkPacks(): Promise<BenchmarkPack[]>

loadUserBenchmarkPacks(userPackDir: string): Promise<BenchmarkPackLoadResult[]>

loadBenchmarkPackFromFile(path: string): Promise<BenchmarkPackLoadResult>

installBenchmarkPackFromFile(path: string, userPackDir: string): Promise<BenchmarkPackInstallResult>

listAvailableBenchmarkPacks(): Promise<BenchmarkPackSummary[]>
```

---

## Load Result Types

Use explicit result objects.

```ts
export type BenchmarkPackLoadResult =
  | {
      ok: true;
      pack: BenchmarkPack;
      source: "built-in" | "user-installed" | "file-preview";
      path?: string;
    }
  | {
      ok: false;
      source: "built-in" | "user-installed" | "file-preview";
      path?: string;
      error: BenchmarkPackValidationError;
    };
```

Install result:

```ts
export type BenchmarkPackInstallResult =
  | {
      ok: true;
      packId: string;
      installedPath: string;
      warnings: string[];
    }
  | {
      ok: false;
      error: BenchmarkPackValidationError;
    };
```

The UI should show validation errors in normal language.

