## Duplicate Pack IDs

If a user imports a pack with an ID that already exists:

Options:
- update existing pack
- install as new version
- cancel

MVP behavior:

```text
If same pack ID and newer version:
  ask user to update.

If same pack ID and same version:
  ask user to replace or cancel.

If same pack ID but different source:
  warn strongly.
```

---

## Versioning

Each pack must include:

```json
{
  "id": "viscose",
  "version": "2026.1"
}
```

Pack version is important because thresholds may change.

Raw runs should store:
- benchmarkId used
- benchmarkVersion used
- scenarioId matched at time of analysis if needed

The engine should be able to re-analyze old runs with newer benchmark data, but it should be transparent when benchmark versions change.

---

## Custom Packs Without Thresholds

Custom packs do not need ranks or thresholds.

Minimum useful custom pack:

```json
{
  "id": "my-practice-pack",
  "name": "My Practice Pack",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "supportedPlatforms": ["aimlabs"],
  "defaultScoringDirection": "higher-is-better",
  "ranks": [],
  "categories": [],
  "scenarios": [
    {
      "id": "microshot-practice",
      "name": "Microshot Practice",
      "platform": "aimlabs",
      "nativeCategory": "Clicking",
      "universalCategory": "static-clicking",
      "hasThresholdData": false
    }
  ],
  "thresholds": []
}
```

The app should still track:
- PB
- latest score
- last-10 average
- trend
- consistency
- volume
- coach notes

It should not show rank.

